; Regression test for issue #664: Value expression regexp matching should return a match object (BZ#664)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/664
; The =~ operator currently returns true/false (boolean), not a match object.
; A match object would allow accessing captured groups like \1, \2, etc.

2024/01/01 Test Payee
    Expenses:Food:Groceries    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg --format '%(account =~ /(.+):(.+)/)\n'
true
true
end test
